<br>
As I clearly stated, you have to KNOW when it's a good time to melee and not. <br>
<br>
And I should have mentioned, yes at the Higher levels, melee becomes more and more usless, since the max you can get with any weapon is 110, making most mobs at those level unhittable. <br>
<br>
But it doesn't mean you can never melee at those levels. You just have to lear to judge the situation.<br>
<br>
But I also suspect most caster give up melee long before they have maxed out thier skills. (But not all, I have talked to other much higher casters that have melee skills at only half of what they can)<br>
<br>
Also, I never said that a wizard (or any caster) should giveup casting, for just melee. Just that it can be a way to extend you mana. <br>
<br>
Basically, I feel if you have a skill that can help out, why not max it out? I've got the spell True North, which I never use, cause with Sense Heading of 170, I don't have to stop and load the spell, cast it, and then change the spell again. <br>
<br>
Good melee skills allow me to also go after things that are much lower for raw materials I need for skills. Rather then burn up mana I can hunt them myself. <br>
<br>
And as stated by another player above, what good is getting a staff or dagger with a really nice proc if your melee skill is say 43? cause at 29, you said, heck with fighting, I'm a caster, I'm to good for that.<br>
<br>
And if you are so against any wizard meleeing, why where you stabbing that phase spider? <br>
<br>
I'm just supporting a players right to PLAY HIS OR HER CHARACTER any way they want. No one has the right to tell another player that they can't play the wat they want to.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ututmosisnakptah.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tutmosis Nak Ptah</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 8<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(9/6/02 12:32:15 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm44.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=79.topic&index=22>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Mighty tank wizards</span><hr size=1> There really is no need to get defensive, as I stated its just my 2cp worth. I was hitting the spider as a joke, you know to get a few laughs, to have fun and not take things to seriously. <br>
<br>
While we are still on this, I might add that when the group you are with is chain pulling you will need all the mana you can get just to stay effective. To me that means medding. Now don’t get me wrong I have cursed my lack of melee skill a couple of times when I have run out of mana while soloing and had to med to finish a mob off that was running away.<br>
<br>
Are there reasons for a Wizard to Melee?  I am sure there are. For me however, I choose not to on the grounds that it just takes way to long to kill something that way.<br>
<br>
