Lies!  It's all Lies!<br>
<br>
Meleeing as a wizard is not going to kill you unless you're the type who normally plunges off the ramp in EK to save travel time.<br>
<br>
At level 55 I'm still meleeing.  I do it for a variety of reasons (not the least of which is RP.) And, my melee DOES contribute to the total success rate of my party (at times.)<br>
<br>
With my maxxed melee skills (thanks buffing party members!) I do hit things often enough to get procs in. I have an entire bag full of weapons with various procs. At the start of some melee mayhem I grab one and drive in to the fray. Some of these things proc minor debuffs, others minor DoTs. Some proc DD. And while I do hit and do help get the baddy's health bar starting to empty out, it never gets me agro.<br>
<br>
I'm far safer meleeing than nuking.  My melee is much less noticable than that of the big brute of a warrior who is hacking and slashing it dead. Well, that is until I get my Skull Shaped Wand (20dam 20dly, procs Ice Comet ((1120 DD)), MR/FR/CR/DiS +5, Evok skill +5%, cold dam. +4, Nec/Wiz/Mage/Ench, All races.)  I think THAT would make me more noticable than all the taunt buttons on Norrath pushed at the same time... then again cast Shock of Snowflake seems to get more agro than a Warlord can gain in an hour.<br>
<br>
-Ephelba Westwitch<br>
