<br>
Well, for most of Sol A, we where fine. But once we started getting deeper, we actually ran into Goblins that gave xp (none conned higher then dark blue). After one battle, an only at half mana (and sitting and resting like a good caster), the Cleric brother pulls a train of 4 goblins. So we start and things are fine, only 2 more join in. Things were looking grim. Rather then just bast away, I mixed a few blasts with melee and  Tishan's clash. Those four extra second can make a difference. Soon 6 goblins were 4 then 3 then 2 and I was OOM, but still doing damage, and once we were down to 1 goblin, I parked it and let my brothers finish it off. <br>
<br>
But there is no doubt that if I hadn't meleed (and hit 80% of the time for 12-22 damage, love that shaded dagger) we would have or at least I would have died. Once I was OOM, if I hadn't had a maxed out piercing skill, and been able to do some damage, all I would have been able to do is stand there taking hit afte hit.<br>
<br>
Same day, later, me and the Cleric brother go after Chief Goonda together. The Chief and the Preistess are up and we pull them both. I root the Chief and down goes the preistess. I start in on the chief and after four blasts (he healed himself partially once) he gives up, and wanders away. I chase after him and melee him to the end. I had enough for a blast, but wanted to save that for the pet. Blast, OOM, melee, melee. One dead pet.<br>
<br>
Now if only a players pet stayed around after the player died and kept fighting that would be nice. What spells do these casters have that allow them to have pets that out live them?<br>
